<font color="#FF0000">THE MONUMENT</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 30  9:53:12 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I have never, ever, anywhere in the world seen a monument<br>
that speaks so laudly to so many people at such personal level!  And yet it gives all
of us a lasting impression of the life, death, war and sacrafice of the service men
and women and their families, regarless if one had any personal connection to the
war.<br><br>
Besides the physical appearance of the Wall, I think Ms. Lin<br>
really created an experience, which is completed by the people visiting the site
bringing it all together, so that the people, the people described on the wall, and
their families, friends and significant others form the monument. It is not just
granite, walkway or landscaping, but together with people participating in it, they
become the monument -- it is a living piece of art and memory of the people. --
Thanks Ms. Lin!
